abstract: >
  The Bitcoin Digital Labor Derivative (DLD) Protocol is a non-custodial,
  Bitcoin-native economic framework that transforms time-locked staking
  and cold storage into a measurable, velocity-aware distribution mechanism.
  The protocol introduces bounded velocity incentives, miner-coordinated
  funding, and a Recession Bypass Index (RBI) to address deflationary pressure
  in automated and AI-accelerated economies, while preserving Bitcoinâ€™s
  decentralization and sovereignty.

